: Sunday final ratings|last=Welch|first=Alex|work=TV by the Numbers|date=January 7, 2020|accessdate=January 7, 2020}}</ref>\n |ShortSummary= When Lois becomes Meg's new music teacher at Adam West High, Connie sees an opportunity to bully Lois, and things get worse when Connie gets expelled and Lois ends up arrested for supposedly murdering her.\n |LineColor=#99FF00\n}}\n{{Episode list/sublist|Family Guy (season 18)\n |EpisodeNumber= 340\n |EpisodeNumber2= 11\n |Title= Short Cuts\n |DirectedBy= [[Julius Wu]]\n |WrittenBy= Kirker Butler\n |OriginalAirDate= {{Start date|2020|2|16}}\n| ProdCode= JACX11\n |Viewers= 1.65<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.showbuzzdaily.com/articles/showbuzzdailys-top-150-sunday-cable-originals-network-finals-2-16-2020.html|title=Updated: ShowBuzzDaily's Top 150 Sunday Cable Originals & Network Finals: 2.16.2020|last=Metcalf|first=Mitch|date=February 19, 2020|work=Showbuzz Daily|accessdate=February 19, 2020}}</ref>\n |ShortSummary= After accidentally foiling a robbery at Mort Goldman's pharmacy, Brian is declared a local hero -- and a blast from Brian's past comes to congratulate him. Meanwhile, Lois gets a pixie cut, leading Peter to do things that Lois finds insane and repulsive.\n |LineColor=#99FF00\n}}\n{{Episode list/sublist|Family Guy (season 18)\n |EpisodeNumber= 341\n |EpisodeNumber2= 12\n |Title= Undergrounded\n |DirectedBy= Greg Colton\n |WrittenBy= Mike Desilets\n |OriginalAirDate= {{Start date|2020|2|23}}\n| ProdCode= JACX13\n |Viewers= 1.57<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.showbuzzdaily.com/articles/showbuzzdailys-top-150-sunday-cable-originals-network-finals-2-23-2020.html|title=Updated: ShowBuzzDaily's Top 150 Sunday Cable Originals & Network Finals: 2.23.2020|last=Metcalf|first=Mitch|date=February 25, 2020|work=Showbuzz Daily|accessdate=February 25, 2020}}</ref>\n |ShortSummary= Lois grounds Peter after discovering his secret credit card, leading him to dig a tunnel to be able to still get outside. After inviting Cleveland, Quagmire and Joe in to the tunnel, it collapses, leaving the four trapped.\n |LineColor=#99FF00\n}}\n{{Episode list/sublist|Family Guy (season 18)\n |EpisodeNumber= 342\n |EpisodeNumber2= 13\n |Title= Rich Old Stewie\n |DirectedBy= Brian Iles\n |WrittenBy= [[Chris Sheridan (writer)|Chris Sheridan]]\n |OriginalAirDate= {{Start date|2020|3|1}}\n| ProdCode= JACX12\n |Viewers= 1.55<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.showbuzzdaily.com/articles/showbuzzdailys-top-150-sunday-cable-originals-network-finals-3-1-2020.html|title=Updated: ShowBuzzDaily's Top 150 Sunday Cable Originals & Network Finals: 3.1.2020|last=Metcalf|first=Mitch|date=March 3, 2020|work=Showbuzz Daily|accessdate=March 3, 2020}}</ref>\n |ShortSummary= Years into the future, Stewie has become rich and respected after abandoning the family when Carter bequeathed his fortune to him rather than Chris. When Brian visits to inform Stewie that Peter is near death and wishes to see his son, Stewie begins a cross-country trek to discover just how far his family have fallen since his departure.\n |LineColor=#99FF00\n}}\n{{Episode list/sublist|Family Guy (season 18)\n |EpisodeNumber= 343\n |EpisodeNumber2= 14\n |Title= The Movement\n |DirectedBy= Joe Vaux\n |WrittenBy= Maggie Mull\n |OriginalAirDate= {{Start date|2020|3|8}}\n| ProdCode= JACX15\n |Viewers= 1.45<ref>{{cite web|url= http://www.showbuzzdaily.com/articles/showbuzzdailys-top-150-sunday-cable-originals-network-finals-3-8-2020.html|title=Updated: ShowBuzzDaily's Top 150 Sunday Cable Originals & Network Finals: 3.8.2020|last=Metcalf|first=Mitch|date=March 10, 2020|work=Showbuzz Daily|accessdate=March 10, 2020}}</ref>\n |ShortSummary= Peter gets a job as a coach for Quahog's minor league baseball team. During a pregame national anthem, he gets severe stomach cramps that bring him to his knees--which leads to everyone declaring him to the new face of American protest against racial injustice.\n |LineColor=#99FF00\n}}\n{{Episode list/sublist|Family Guy (season 18)\n |EpisodeNumber= 344\n |EpisodeNumber2= 15\n |Title= Baby Stewie\n |DirectedBy= Jerry Langford\n |WrittenBy= Artie Johann\n |OriginalAirDate= {{Start date|2020|3|15}}\n| ProdCode= JACX14\n |Viewers= 1.68<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.showbuzzdaily.com/articles/showbuzzdailys-top-150-sunday-cable-originals-network-finals-3-15-2020.html|title=Updated: ShowBuzzDaily's Top 150 Sunday Cable Originals & Network Finals: 3.15.2020|last=Metcalf|first=Mitch|date=March 17, 2020|work=Showbuzz Daily|accessdate=March 17, 2020}}</ref>\n |ShortSummary=Tired of Stewie telling him that he\u2019s smarter than him, Brian tells Stewie that once he hits puberty, he\u2019ll start to get dumb like Chris. So Stewie plans to alter his DNA to be smart  forever, but the experiment backfires and turns him into an actual ordinary infant.\n |LineColor=#99FF00\n}}\n{{Episode list/sublist|Family Guy (season 18)\n |EpisodeNumber= 345\n |EpisodeNumber2= 16\n |Title=Start Me Up\n |RTitle=<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.foxflash.com/releases/view/week-of-apr-12-19-2020|title=Fox schedule week of April 12-19, 2020|accessdate=26 March 2020}}</ref>\n |DirectedBy= \n |WrittenBy= \n |OriginalAirDate= {{Start date|2020|4|19}}\n |ProdCode= JACX16\n |Viewers=\n |ShortSummary= \n |LineColor=#99FF00\n}}\n{{Episode list/sublist|Family Guy (season 18)\n |EpisodeNumber= 346\n |EpisodeNumber2= 17\n |Title= Coma Guy\n |DirectedBy= \n |WrittenBy= \n |OriginalAirDate= {{Start date|2020|4|26}}<ref>{{cite web|url=http://thefutoncritic.com/listings/20200402fox20/&date=04/26/2020|title=(FG-1707) \"Coma Guy\"|website=The Futon Critic|accessdate=April 2, 2020}}</ref>\n |ProdCode= JACX07<ref>Reg. # PAu003929680 at \n[http://cocatalog.loc.gov/cgi-bin/Pwebrecon.cgi?DB=local&PAGE=First U.S. Copyright Records database] {{Webarchive|url=https://archive.is/20120629083507/http://cocatalog.loc.gov/cgi-bin/Pwebrecon.cgi?DB=local&PAGE=First |date=2012-06-29 }}.</ref>\n |Viewers=\n |ShortSummary= \n |LineColor=#99FF00\n}}\n{{Episode list/sublis