d-derby-tv-awards-winners-2019-game-of-thrones-fleabag-news/|website=[[Gold Derby]]|access-date=April 5, 2020|date=September 18, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200406001043/https://www.goldderby.com/article/2019/gold-derby-tv-awards-winners-2019-game-of-thrones-fleabag-news/|archive-date=April 5, 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" rowspan=\"2\"| [[Nickelodeon Kids' Choice Awards|Kids' Choice Awards]]\n| rowspan=\"2\"| [[2020 Kids' Choice Awards|TBA]]\n| Favorite Reality Show\n| ''The Masked Singer''\n| {{pending}}\n| style=text-align:center;\" rowspan=\"2\"| <ref>{{cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2020/02/avengers-end-game-leads-nickelodeons-kids-choice-awards-nominations-billie-eilish-taylor-swift-chance-the-rapper-full-list-1202859259/|title=''Avengers: Endgame'' Leads Nickelodeon\u2019s Kids\u2019 Choice Awards Nominations; Chance The Rapper Set As Host|work=[[Deadline Hollywood]]|author=Denise Petski|date=February 13, 2020|access-date=March 26, 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200313113934/https://deadline.com/2020/02/avengers-end-game-leads-nickelodeons-kids-choice-awards-nominations-billie-eilish-taylor-swift-chance-the-rapper-full-list-1202859259/|archive-date=March 13, 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n|-\n| Favorite TV Host\n| [[Nick Cannon]]\n| {{pending}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| [[MTV Movie & TV Awards]]\n| [[2019 MTV Movie & TV Awards|2019]]\n| Best Host\n| Nick Cannon\n| {{nominated}}\n| style=text-align:center;\"| <ref>{{cite web|last=Bell|first=Crystal|title=2019 MTV Movie & TV Awards Winners: See the Full List|url=https://www.mtv.ca/mtv-movie-and-tv-awards-winners/|website=[[MTV]]|access-date=June 20, 2019|date=June 17, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190620221134/https://www.mtv.ca/mtv-movie-and-tv-awards-winners/|archive-date=June 20, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" rowspan=\"2\"| [[People's Choice Awards]]\n| rowspan=\"2\"| [[45th People's Choice Awards|2019]]\n| The Competition Show of 2019\n| ''The Masked Singer''\n| {{nominated}}\n| style=text-align:center;\" rowspan=\"2\"| <ref>{{cite web|last=Evans|first=Greg|title=E! People\u2019s Choice Awards Finalists Announced; Voting Open Through Oct. 18 \u2013 Complete List|url=https://deadline.com/2019/09/e-peoples-choice-awards-finalists-complete-list-1202710461|website=[[Deadline Hollywood]]|access-date=April 3, 2020|date=September 4, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190914161428/https://deadline.com/2019/09/e-peoples-choice-awards-finalists-complete-list-1202710461/|archive-date=September 14, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n|-\n| The Competition Contestant of 2019\n| [[T-Pain]]\n| {{nominated}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| [[Producers Guild of America Award|Producers Guild of America Awards]]\n| [[31st Producers Guild of America Awards|2020]]\n| Outstanding Producer of Game & Competition Television \n| Craig Plestis, Izzie Pick Ibarra, Nikki Varhely-Gillingham, Rosie Seitchik, Stacey Thomas-Muir, Nick Cannon, Ashley Sylvester, Lindsay Tuggle, Pete Cooksley, Chelsea Candelaria, Anne Chanthavong, Zo\u00eb Ritchken, Deena Katz, Erin Brady, Jeff Kmiotek, Lexi Shoemaker\n| {{nominated}}\n| style=text-align:center;\"| <ref>{{cite web|title=Nominations Announced in Motion Pictures and Television Programs Categories - 2020 Awards|url=https://www.producersguild.org/news/483748/|website=[[Producers Guild of America]]|access-date=April 3, 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200215044411/https://www.producersguild.org/news/483748/|archive-date=February 15, 2020|date=January 7, 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| [[Brunico Communications|Realscreen Awards]]\n| 2020\n| Talent & Studio-Based Competition\n| ''The Masked Singer''\n| {{won}}\n| style=text-align:center;\"| <ref>{{cite web|title=2020 Winners & Nominees|url=https://awards.realscreen.com/Winners/Winner/2020|website=Realscreen|publisher=[[Brunico Communications]]|access-date=April 5, 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200405233615/https://awards.realscreen.com/Winners/Winner/2020|archive-date=April 5, 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| [[Shorty Awards]]\n| [[11th Shorty Awards|2019]]\n| Best in Entertainment Sites and Apps \n| ''The Masked Singer'' Social Hub\n| {{nominated}}\n| style=text-align:center;\"| <ref>{{cite web|title=''The Masked Singer'' Social Hub |url=https://shortyawards.com/11th/the-masked-singer-social-hub|website=[[Shorty Awards]]|access-date=April 5, 2019|date=January 28, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200405064238/https://shortyawards.com/11th/the-masked-singer-social-hub|archive-date=April 5, 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| [[Teen Choice Awards]]\n| [[2019 Teen Choice Awards|2019]]\n| Choice Reality TV Show\n| ''The Masked Singer''\n| {{nominated}}\n| style=text-align:center;\"| <ref>{{cite web|last=Kaufran|first=Gil|title=Lil Nas X & Post Malone Lead 2019 Teen Choice Awards Nominations: See the List|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/awards/8516707/2019-teen-choice-awards-nominations|website=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|access-date=April 3, 2020|date=June 19, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200326005330/https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/awards/8516707/2019-teen-choice-awards-nominations|archive-date=March 26, 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n|-\n|}\n\n===Critical response===\n''[[Entertainment Weekly]]''<nowiki>'</nowiki>s Kristen Baldwin felt the show was captivating but said the judges were unfit to be critiquing singers and criticized them for not paying attention to the clues or performances.<ref>{{cite web|last=Baldwin|first=Kristen|title=Fox's ''The Masked Singer'': What the holy hell is this?|url=https://ew.com/tv-reviews/2019/01/02/the-masked-singer-fox-recap/|website=[[Entertainment Weekly]]|access-date=April 4, 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190920204236/https://ew.com/tv-reviews/2019/01/02/the-masked-singer-fox-recap/|archive-date=April 20, 2019|date=January 2, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> Likewise, Kelly Lawler of ''[[USA Today]]'' attributed the series' success to its brilliant concept only and named the judging panel the worst in reality television history. She described Jeong as {{nobr|over-the-top}}, Scherzinger as boring, Thicke as too serious, and McCarthy as inexperienced<ref>{{cite web|last=Lawler|first=Kelly|title=The 5 best (and 5 worst) reality-TV show judging panels of all time|url=https://www.usatoday.com/story/life/tv/2019/02/25/reality-tv-judges-5-best-and-5-worst-panels-all-time-the-voice-american-idol-simon-cowell-rupaul/2937947002/|website=[[USA Today]]|access-date=April 4, 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200401114701/https://www.usatoday.com/story/life/tv/2019/02/25/reality-tv-judges-5-best-and-5-worst-panels-all-time-the-voice-american-idol-simon-cowell-rupaul/2937947002/|archive-date=April 1, 2020|date=February 25, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> Similarly, [[Matt Zoller Seitz]] of ''Vulture'' lambasted the presence of McCarthy as a judge (referring to her {{nobr|[[Jenny McCarthy#Autism activism and views on vaccines|prominent]] [[vaccine hesitancy|anti-vaccine]]}} views) but praised the chemistry between her and the other judges. He criticized the way the show's producers edit their guesses, stating they should cut out repetitive comments more often.<ref>{{cite web|last=Seitz|first=Matt Zoller|author-link=Matt Zoller Seitz|title=How Is The Masked Singer Real?|url=https://www.vulture.com/2019/09/the-masked-singer-season-2-review.html|website=Vulture|access-date=April 4, 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191218162823/https://www.vulture.com/2019/09/the-masked-singer-season-2-review.html|archive-date=December 18, 2019|date=September 26, 2019|url-status=live|url-access=subscription}}</ref> Others from ''Vulture'' also derided the editing as awkward but praised the costumes as fantastic and noted that they came to life on stage, describing the timelessness of the Egg, gorgeousness of the Butterfly, and badass attitude of the Rottweiler. However, they felt the judges were mindless and unfunny, condemning them for spoiling the show's innovative concept with distracting statements.<ref>{{cite web|last=Wright|first=Megh|title=Egg Was Too Pure for This Terrible World|url=https://www.vulture.com/2019/09/goodbye-egg.html|website=Vulture|access-date=April 4, 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190926201418/https://www.vulture.com/2019/09/goodbye-egg.html|archive-date=September 26, 2019|date=September 26, 2019|url-status=live|url-access=subscription}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last=VanArendonk|first=Kathryn|title=''The Masked Singer'' Is a Reality-TV Fever Dream|url=https://www.vulture.com/2019/01/the-masked-singer-fox-review.html|website=Vulture|access-date=April 4, 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191225230817/https://www.vulture.com/2019/01/the-masked-singer-fox-review.html|archive-date=December 25, 2019|date=January 2, 2019|url-status=live|url-access=subscription}}</ref>\n\nAfter attended a taping of the show, Kayla Keegan of ''[[Good Housekeeping]]'' said she appreciated the detailing of the costumes, praising Toybina's skill in designing them.<ref name=\"GH Feb 6\"/>  Writing for ''[[The Atlantic]]'', Megan Garber compared the series' format to that of [[Police procedural|crime procedural]] ''[[CSI: Crime Scene Investigation|CSI]]'' due to its mystery elements.<ref name=\"ATL Feb 28\">{{cite news|last=Garber|first=Megan|title=''The Masked Singer'' Lets You In on the Scam|url=https://www.theatlantic.com/entertainment/archive/2019/02/masked-singer-finale-what-show-really-reveals/583882/|website=[[The Atlantic]]|access-date=April 5, 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200308121421/https://www.theatlantic.com/entertainment/archive/2019/02/masked-singer-finale-what-show-really-reveals/583882/|archive-date=March 8, 2020|date=February 28, 2019|url-status=live|url-access=limited}}</ref> Emily Yahr of ''[[The Washington Post]]'' described the show as crazy but said Cannon was perfect as host, noting his years of experience in the same role on ''[[America's Got Talent]]''.<ref>{{cite web|last=Yahr|first=Emily|title=Yes, that was real life: ''The Masked Singer'' premiered and was even weirder than you imagined|url=https://www.vulture.com/2019/01/the-masked-singer-fox-review.html|website=Vulture|access-date=April 4, 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191225230817/https://www.vulture.com/2019/01/the-masked-singer-fox-review.html|archive-date=December 25, 2019|date=January 2, 2019|url-status=live|url-access=subscription}}</ref> Conversely, ''[[The Globe and Mail]]''<nowiki>'</nowiki>s [[John Doyle (critic)|John Doyle]] called Cannon inarticulate and described the judges as [[Camp (style)|cheesy]] and irrelevant. He characterized the show as a wacky and dumb version of [[Charades]] but acknowledged that it is popular because of its simplicity. Doyle cited the series as an example of a cultural shift in the United States away from the competitive and often exploitative nature of shows such as ''[[American Idol]]'' towards a higher level of positivity among reality television series.<ref>{{cite web|last=Doyle|first=John|author-link=John Doyle (critic)|title=Dumb simplicity: Why The Masked Singer is a massive TV hit|url=https://www.theglobeandmail.com/arts/television/article-dumb-simplicity-why-the-masked-singer-is-a-massive-tv-hit/|website=[[The Globe and Mail]]|access-date=April 4, 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191218163655/https://www.theglobeandmail.com/arts/television/article-dumb-simplicity-why-the-masked-singer-is-a-massive-tv-hit/|archive-date=December 18, 2019|date=November 4, 2019|url-status=live|url-access=subscription}}</ref> Likewise, Daniel D'Addario of ''[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]'' described the show as relaxing and refreshing, calling it a return to form for television as the series possesses the now-rare ability to uplift and unite people. He commended the show's judges, comparing them to the original ''American Idol'' judges as non-experts in their fields, noting their common, implausible [[A-list]] celebrity guesses. He also praised the show's positive platform for allowing celebrities to express themselves freely even if they are not professional singers.<ref>{{cite web|last=D'Addario|first=Daniel|title=In Praise of ''The Masked Singer'', TV's Last Uniter (Column)|url=https://variety.com/2020/tv/columns/masked-singer-super-bowl-1203485315/|website=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]|access-date=April 4, 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200210183913/https://variety.com/2020/tv/columns/masked-singer-super-bowl-1203485315/|archive-date=February 10, 2020|date=February 1, 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n===Cultural impact===\nFans of the show take part in guessing on [[Twitter]] each time an episode airs.<ref name=\"E! Feb 27\"/> The series is discussed on numerous [[podcast|podcasts]] and has generated its own [[Reddit#Subreddit|thread]] on [[Reddit]].<ref name=\"ATL Feb 28\"/> \n\nMichael Schneider of ''Variety'' said the series' success has sparked a revitalization of reality television in the United States, comparing it to [[Fox Broadcasting Company#2000s: Rise to ratings leadership, the American Idol effect, and fierce rivalry with CBS|the early 2000s]] when Fox's many reality series received high ratings. The revivals of ''[[Paradise Hotel]]'' and ''[[Temptation Island]]'' by Fox and [[USA Network]], respectively, have been credited to the show's success, as have the American versions of ''[[Love Island (American TV series)|Love Island]]'' and ''[[I Can See Your Voice (American game show)|I Can See Your Voice]]''. Rob Wade, the President of Fox Alternative Entertainment, has described a shift in the way new shows are [[sales presentation|pitched]] since the series premiered, noting there is an increased openness to new ideas. Wade also said the heads of almost all television networks thanked him for the series giving them a \"[[blank cheque|carte blanche]]\" to take new programming risks.<ref name=\"VAR Feb 19\">{{cite news|last=Schneider|first=Michael|title=Who Is That Masked B-Lister?|url=https://www.newspapers.com/clip/48002572/the-gazette/|work=[[Montreal Gazette]]|agency=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]|access-date=April 4, 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200404200853/https://www.newspapers.com/clip/48002572/the-gazette/|archive-date=April 4, 2020|date=February 19, 2019|url-status=live|via=[[Ancestry.com#Newspapers.com|Newspapers.com]]}}</ref>\n\nThe show was the first in the [[Masked Singer|''Masked Singer'' franchise]] to air outside of Asia and its success has been attributed to at least ten local adaptations of the series, including versions in [[The Masked Singer Austria|Austria]], Peru, and the [[The Masked Singer (British TV series)|United Kingdom]]. The producers of the British series said they were inspired to adapt the format after watching an episode of the American version.<ref name=\"THR Jan 2\"/><ref name=\"GH Feb 6\"/> The series has also been credited with reinvigorating the costume genre of television. Interest in adapting other costume-centered franchises such as ''[[Wild Things (game show)|Wild Things]]'' and ''[[Sexy Beasts]]'' has increased around the world since the show premiered.<ref name=\"TBI Apr 5\"/>\n\n===Television ratings===\n''The Masked Singer'' premiered in {{nobr|January 2019}} as the highest rated [[reality television|unscripted]] television series debut since ''[[The X Factor (American TV series)|The X Factor]]'' in 2011. Following three days of DVR viewing, the first episode's {{nobr|18\u201349 rating}} grew by {{nobr|30 percent\u2014the}} highest increase ever for a premiere in the show's genre.<ref>{{cite web|last=Holloway|first=Daniel|title=''The Masked Singer'' Scores Biggest Live+3 Lift Ever for Unscripted Series|url=https://variety.com/2019/tv/news/masked-singer-ratings-1203101918/|website=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]|access-date=March 29, 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200125164644/https://variety.com/2019/tv/news/masked-singer-ratings-1203101918/|archive-date=December 22, 2019|date=January 25, 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> Although initially dropping, ratings grew towards the end of the season, and the finale became the most watched episode.<ref name=\"ADW Sep 25\">{{cite web|last=Lynch|first=Jason|title=How Freshman Hit ''The Masked Singer'' Will Try to Avoid a Sophomore Slump|url=https://www.adweek.com/tv-video/masked-singer-season-2-what-to-expect/|website=[[Adweek]]|access-date=March 29, 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190926021058/https://www.adweek.com/tv-video/masked-singer-season-2-what-to-expect/|archive-date=September 26, 2019|date=September 25, 2019|url-status=live|url-access=subscription}}</ref> The show concluded the [[2018\u201319 United States network television schedule|2018\u201319 television season]] as the highest rated new series among adults {{nobr|18\u201349}}, averaging a {{nobr|2.6 rating}} throughout all ten episodes,<ref name=\"THR May 23\"/> and as the highest rated entertainment series among teens, {{nobr|men 18\u201334,}} {{nobr|adults 18\u201334,}} and {{nobr|adults 18\u201349.}}<ref name=\"ADW Oct 20\">{{cite web|title=The 2019 TV Hot List: The Year\u2019s Biggest and Buzziest Shows, Networks and People|url=https://www.adweek.com/tv-video/the-2019-tv-hot-list-the-years-biggest-and-buzziest-shows-networks-and-people/4/|website=[[Adweek]]|access-date=April 4, 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191230042701/https://www.adweek.com/tv-video/the-2019-tv-hot-list-the-years-biggest-and-buzziest-shows-networks-and-people/4/|archive-date=December 30, 2019|date=October 20, 2019|url-status=live|url-access=subscription}}</ref> Among unscripted series, it was the first to rank {{nobr|number-one}} in the genre in its first season since ''[[Joe Millionaire]]'' in 2003.<ref name=\"VAR Feb 19\"/> \n\nThe second season premiered {{nobr|17 percent}} lower than the previous, though it was mostly in line with the first season's average.<ref>{{cite web|last=Thorne|first=Will|title=TV Ratings: ''The Masked Singer'' Easily Wins Wednesday|url=https://variety.com/2019/tv/news/tv-ratings-the-masked-singer-season-2-premiere-1203350350/|website=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]|access-date=March 29, 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190927145835/https://variety.com/2019/tv/news/tv-ratings-the-masked-singer-season-2-premiere-1203350350/|archive-date=September 27, 2019|date=September 26, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> The finale's ratings also dropped compared to the first season, although the broadcast was up {{nobr|20 percent}} in viewers from the previous week.<ref>{{cite web|last=Ramos|first=Dino-Ray|title=''The Masked Singer'' & ''Survivor'' Finales, ''Live In Front Of A Studio Audience'' Ratings Dip Amid Primetime Impeachment Vote|url=https://deadline.com/2019/12/the-masked-singer-finale-ratings-survivor-winner-live-in-front-of-a-studio-audience-1202813754/|website=[[Deadline Hollywood]]|access-date=March 29, 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200304071423/https://deadline.com/2019/12/the-masked-singer-finale-ratings-survivor-winner-live-in-front-of-a-studio-audience-1202813754/|archive-date=March 4, 2020|date=December 19, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> [[Deadline Hollywood]] cited the second season as a major reason why {{nobr|Fox\u2014for}} the first time in the network's {{nobr|history\u2014ranked}} number-one in fall entertainment programming,<ref>{{cite web|last1=Andreeva|first1=Nellie||last2=Hipes|first2=Patrick|title=Fox Tops Fall Demo Ratings For First Time In Decade; NBC Snaps CBS\u2019 Total Viewers Streak|url=https://deadline.com/2019/12/tv-ratings-fall-2019-fox-wins-nbc-the-masked-singer-sunday-night-football-1202817673/|website=[[Deadline Hollywood]]|access-date=April 4, 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200104191044/https://deadline.com/2019/12/tv-ratings-fall-2019-fox-wins-nbc-the-masked-singer-sunday-night-football-1202817673/|archive-date=January 4, 2020|date=December 27, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> and ''[[Adweek]]'' named the show the \"Hottest {{nobr|Reality/Competition}} Series\" of 2019.<ref name=\"ADW Oct 20\"/> The third season, which premiered as the [[Super Bowl LIV]] [[list of Super Bowl lead-out programs|lead-out program]], was viewed by over {{nobr|23.7 million}} people and received an {{nobr|8.1 18\u201349 rating}}. While the episode was watched by more than the previous lead-out, ''[[The World's Best]]'' {{nobr|(22.2 million),}} and Fox's most-recent lead-out, 2017's ''[[24: Legacy]]'' {{nobr|(17.6 million),}} it was lower than the viewership of ''[[This Is Us]]'' {{nobr|(27 million)}} in 2018.<ref>{{cite web|last=Adalian|first=Joseph|title=23 Million People Watched a Celebrity Pretend to Be a Robot on ''The Masked Singer''|url=https://www.vulture.com/2020/02/the-masked-singer-super-bowl-ratings.html|website=[[New York (magazine)#Digital expansion and destination sites|Vulture]]|access-date=March 29, 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200311162320/https://www.vulture.com/2020/02/the-masked-singer-super-bowl-ratings.html|archive-date=March 11, 2020|date=February 3, 2020|url-status=live|url-access=subscription}}</ref> According to ''[[Ad Age]]'', the series was one of two non-NFL programs to cost at least $200,000 per thirty seconds of advertising during the [[2019\u201320 United States network television schedule|2019\u201320 television season]].<ref>{{cite web|last=Adgate|first=Brad|title=TV Ad Rates (But Not Ad Revenue) Are Dropping|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/bradadgate/2019/10/15/tv-ad-rates-but-not-ad-revenue-are-dropping/|website=[[Forbes]]|access-date=April 8, 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200408171217/https://www.forbes.com/sites/bradadgate/2019/10/15/tv-ad-rates-but-not-ad-revenue-are-dropping/|archive-date=April 8, 2020|date=October 15, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|-\n! style=\"width:7%;\" rowspan=\"2\" | Season\n! style=\"width:14%;\" rowspan=\"2\" | Timeslot\n([[Eastern Time Zone (North America)|ET]], [[UTC\u20135]])\n! style=\"width:7%;\" rowspan=\"2\" | Episodes\n! colspan=\"2\" | First aired\n! colspan=\"2\" | Last aired\n! style=\"width:7%;\" rowspan=\"2\" | TV season\n! style=\"width:28%;\" colspan=\"4\" | Averages\n|-\n! style=\"width:10%;\" | Date\n! style=\"width:8%;\" | Viewers<br>(millions)\n! style=\"width:10%;\" | Date\n! style=\"width:8%;\" | Viewers<br>(millions)\n! style=\"width:7%; | Viewership<br>ranking\n! style=\"width:7%; | Viewers<br>(millions)\n! style=\"width:7%; | 18\u201349<br>ranking\n! style=\"width:7%; | 18\u201349<br>rating\n|-\n| [[The Masked Singer (American season 1)|1]]\n| Wednesday 9:00&nbsp;p.m.\n| 10\n| January 2, 2019\n| 9.37<ref>{{cite web|last=Pucci|first=Douglas|url=https://programminginsider.com/wednesday-final-ratings-the-masked-singer-on-fox-scores-tvs-highest-rated-unscripted-series-launch-in-seven-years/|title=Wednesday Final Ratings: ''The Masked Singer'' on Fox Scores TV\u2019s Highest-Rated Unscripted Series Launch in Seven Years|work=Programming Insider|date=January 4, 2019|access-date=March 27, 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190323022456/https://programminginsider.com/wednesday-final-ratings-the-masked-singer-on-fox-scores-tvs-highest-rated-unscripted-series-launch-in-seven-years/|archive-date=March 23, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n| February 27, 2019\n| 11.48<ref>{{cite web|last=Pucci|first=Douglas|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190403155952/https://programminginsider.com/wednesday-final-ratings-michael-cohen-hearing-draws-significant-audience-figures-in-daytime-across-various-networks/|title=Wednesday Final Ratings: Michael Cohen Hearing Draws Significant Audience Figures in Daytime Across Various Networks|work=Programmi